  {
    "id": "work-032",
    "title_zh": "《沁园春・雪》瓷屏",
    "title_en": "Snow: Porcelain Screen",
    "year": "",
    "material_zh": "瓷",
    "material_en": "Porcelain",
    "project_zh": "毛泽东诗词精选",
    "project_en": "Selected Mao Zedong Poems",
    "size_zh": "",
    "size_en": "",
    "location_zh": "",
    "location_en": "",
    "description_zh": "文字内容：\n北国风光，千里冰封，万里雪飘。望长城内外，惟余莽莽；大河上下，顿失滔滔。山舞银蛇，原驰蜡象，欲与天公试比高。须晴日，看红装素裹，分外妖娆。\n江山如此多娇，引无数英雄竞折腰。惜秦皇汉武，略输文采；唐宗宋祖，稍逊风骚。一代天骄，成吉思汗，只识弯弓射大雕。俱往矣，数风流人物，还看今朝。",
    "description_en": "Text:\nNorthern scenery: a thousand miles sealed in ice, ten thousand miles of drifting snow. Looking within and beyond the Great Wall, there is only boundless whiteness; up and down the great river, the surging waters suddenly fall silent. The mountains dance like silver snakes, the highlands charge like waxen elephants, all seeming to vie with heaven in height. On a clear day, wrapped in red sunlight and white snow, the land appears especially enchanting.\nSuch a magnificent country has inspired countless heroes to bow before it. Alas, Qin Shi Huang and Han Wu were somewhat lacking in literary grace; Emperor Taizong of Tang and Emperor Taizu of Song fell a little short in poetic brilliance. Genghis Khan, that proud son of heaven, knew only how to bend his bow and shoot the great eagle. All are past. To find truly great figures, one must look to the present age.",
    "inspiration_zh": "题记：\n《沁园春・雪》，毛泽东\n张满堂写于2025年",
    "inspiration_en": "Inscription:\nSnow (Tune: Qin Yuan Chun), by Mao Zedong\nWritten by Zhang Mantang in 2025",
    "cover_image": "/images/works/work-032/cover.webp",
    "gallery_images": []
  },
